a:["$","a",null,{"href":"https://futurepulse.hr","target":"_blank","rel":"noopener noreferrer","className":"flex items-center gap-1 hover:text-accent-cyan transition-colors","children":[["$","svg",null,{"xmlns":"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg","width":24,"height":24,"viewBox":"0 0 24 24","fill":"none","stroke":"currentColor","strokeWidth":2,"strokeLinecap":"round","strokeLinejoin":"round","className":"lucide lucide-external-link w-3 h-3","aria-hidden":"true","children":[["$","path","1q9fwt",{"d":"M15 3h6v6"}],["$","path","gplh6r",{"d":"M10 14 21 3"}],["$","path","a6xqqp",{"d":"M18 13v6a2 2 0 0 1-2 2H5a2 2 0 0 1-2-2V8a2 2 0 0 1 2-2h6"}],"$undefined"]}],"Future Pulse"]}]
b:["$","div",null,{"className":"article-enter-delay-2","children":["$","div",null,{"className":"glass-card overflow-hidden mb-8 !hover:transform-none","children":["$","img",null,{"src":"/images/articles/claudes-memory-upgrade-a-real-switch-incentive-or-/main.jpg","alt":"Claude’s memory upgrade: A real switch incentive or just catch-up?","className":"w-full h-auto max-h-[400px] object-cover"}]}]}]
c:["$","div",null,{"className":"article-enter-delay-3 article-prose max-w-none","children":[["$","p",null,{"children":["For months, the AI chatbot wars have been fought on two fronts: raw capability and ",["$","em",null,{"children":"stickiness"}],". OpenAI’s ",["$","a",null,{"href":"https://openai.com/chatgpt","children":"ChatGPT"}]," leverages its head start with plugins and custom GPTs; Google’s ",["$","a",null,{"href":"https://gemini.google.com/","children":"Gemini"}]," banks on deep integration with Workspace; Mistral and others bet on openness. Now, Anthropic is playing the ",["$","strong",null,{"children":"switcher card"}],"—not by out-innovating rivals, but by slashing a key friction point: the hassle of migrating your chat history and prompts."]}],"\n",["$","p",null,{"children":["The update, ",["$","a",null,{"href":"https://www.theverge.com/2024/5/15/24156783/anthropic-claude-memory-free-plan-import-tool","children":["reported by ",["$","em",null,{"children":"The Verge"}]]}],", brings Claude’s memory feature to free users (previously a Pro-tier perk) and adds a dedicated tool to import data from other chatbots. The pitch is straightforward: if you’re tired of starting from scratch every time you test a new AI, Claude will now remember your past interactions—and let you drag your old chats along for the ride."]}],"\n",["$","p",null,{"children":["This isn’t about flashy new features. It’s about ",["$","strong",null,{"children":"reducing the cost of curiosity"}],". Right now, switching AI tools often means losing context: your half-finished code snippets, your refined prompt templates, your iterative research threads. Anthropic’s gambit is that users will jump ship if the onboarding feels like an upgrade, not a reset. Early signals suggest the tool supports imports from ChatGPT, Gemini, and others, though the ",["$","a",null,{"href":"https://support.anthropic.com/en/articles/9999999-claude-memory-faq","children":"fine print"}]," on format compatibility and data limits remains unclear."]}],"\n",["$","p",null,{"children":["The timing is deliberate. AI power users—developers, researchers, and prompt engineers—are increasingly ",["$","strong",null,{"children":"multi-homing"}],", bouncing between tools for specific tasks. But casual users, the bulk of the market, still default to whatever’s easiest. If Claude can position itself as the ",["$","em",null,{"children":"least disruptive"}]," alternative, it might win over the fence-sitters."]}],"\n",["$","div",null,{"className":"not-prose my-8 pt-6 border-t border-white/10","children":[null,["$","div",null,{"className":"glass-card overflow-hidden mb-4 !hover:transform-none","children":["$","img",null,{"src":"/images/articles/claudes-memory-upgrade-a-real-switch-incentive-or-/subtitle.jpg","alt":"Free memory, paid loyalty: the economics of AI switching costs","className":"w-full h-auto max-h-[400px] object-cover"}]}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-text-secondary italic text-lg leading-relaxed font-medium","children":"Free memory, paid loyalty: the economics of AI switching costs"}]]}],"\n",["$","p",null,{"children":["Yet the bigger question isn’t whether the import tool ",["$","em",null,{"children":"works"}],", but whether it ",["$","em",null,{"children":"matters"}],". Memory features and data portability are fast becoming table stakes. OpenAI already offers ",["$","a",null,{"href":"https://help.openai.com/en/articles/7039786-sharing-and-exporting-chats","children":"shared chat links"}]," (albeit clunkily), and third-party tools like ",["$","a",null,{"href":"https://promptperfect.jina.ai/","children":"PromptPerfect"}]," let users manage prompts across platforms. Anthropic’s advantage here is native integration—but for how long?"]}],"\n","$L14","\n","$L15","\n","$L16"]}]
